> I have a 1965 13 window bus....
> which bumpers should it have ?? pointed or the slash ones ?

Only Heinz Nordhoff knows for sure, but he died in 1968.  You might
organize a seance, or read
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/032960.html
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/043472.html
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/029942.html
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/060158.html
http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/060148.html ,
or go to http://www.type2.com/archive/search-vintagebus.html and search
for "slash bumpers".

> and the side pop-outs are out ,
> what size screws to attach the frame to the hinge ?

Per http://www.type2.com/archive/vintagebus/003603.html , M3.5 x 5,
flat head, slotted.  (3.5 mm diameter by 5 mm long.  Dunno
about the thread pitch.)  http://oacdp.freeweb7.com/5867part/451.png
and http://oacdp.freeweb7.com/5867part/455.png concur; if you want to
make someone laugh, visit your friendly local VW dealer and ask for part
number N 10 905 1.  (The parts list main page is
http://oacdp.freeweb7.com/5867part.html ).

Matt Roberds
